  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6960.28 sitting just above the massive +19.4B gamma wall at 6950, dealers are in active selling mode to hedge their long gamma positions, creating immediate resistance. The PIN regime with 137.9B total GEX suggests strong mean-reverting forces, with dealers providing liquidity by selling this proximity to max gamma and buying any dips toward the 6900 support wall. Watch for continued dealer selling pressure into the 6950-7000 gamma cluster, with downside support emerging if price approaches the 6900 level or deeper toward the GEX flip at 6847.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect sellers to step in near current levels with support building on any dips toward 6900-6950.",
